	  <h1 align="center">About Judith E. Wilson</h1>
      <p align="justify">Judith Ellen Wilson was an Irishwoman from County Limerick 
        and a cousin of Lord Rothermere: when her parents died she inherited a 
        large fortune.</p>
      <p align="justify">She had always been devoted to the theatre and the arts 
        generally. She founded a lectureship in the University of Cambridge to 
        bring together those interested in the academic study of drama and poetry 
        and those who were practitioners in these fields. She hoped that the Fellowship 
        would be used also to draw the live theatre and the university closer 
        together.</p>
      <p align="justify">She was a friend of Dame Edith Evans and when Edith Evans 
        lost her husband, Judith Wilson provided a beautiful home at Goudhurst 
        and all the support that an artist needs. Judith Wilson died of cancer 
        at a comparatively early age, and she left her money to Edith Evans in 
        trust and afterwards to the University of Cambridge. On the death of Edith 
        Evans in 1976 the legacy, increased by some valuable works of art, made 
        this fund a unique source of support for work in drama and poetry.&nbsp;</p>
